19Ps 11:1 [For the choir director£∫ A psalm of David.] I trust in the LORD for protection. So why do you say to me, "Fly like a bird to the mountains for safety!
19Ps 11:2 The wicked are stringing their bows and fitting their arrows on the bowstrings. They shoot from the shadows at those whose hearts are right.
19Ps 11:3 The foundations of law and order have collapsed. What can the righteous do?"
19Ps 11:4 But the LORD is in his holy Temple; the LORD still rules from heaven. He watches everyone closely, examining every person on earth.
19Ps 11:5 The LORD examines both the righteous and the wicked. He hates those who love violence.
19Ps 11:6 He will rain down blazing coals and burning sulfur on the wicked, punishing them with scorching winds.
19Ps 11:7 For the righteous LORD loves justice. The virtuous will see his face.
19Ps 12:1 [For the choir director£∫ A psalm of David, to be accompanied by an eight-stringed instrument®Á.] Help, O LORD, for the godly are fast disappearing! The faithful have vanished from the earth! / ®ÁHebrew according to the sheminith
19Ps 12:2 Neighbors lie to each other, speaking with flattering lips and deceitful hearts.
19Ps 12:3 May the LORD cut off their flattering lips and silence their boastful tongues.
19Ps 12:4 They say, "We will lie to our hearts' content. Our lips are our own - who can stop us?"
19Ps 12:5 The LORD replies, "I have seen violence done to the helpless, and I have heard the groans of the poor. Now I will rise up to rescue them, as they have longed for me to do."
19Ps 12:6 The LORD's promises are pure, like silver refined in a furnace, purified seven times over.
19Ps 12:7 Therefore, LORD, we know you will protect the oppressed, preserving them forever from this lying generation,
19Ps 12:8 even though the wicked strut about, and evil is praised throughout the land.
19Ps 13:1 [For the choir director£∫ A psalm of David.] O LORD, how long will you forget me? Forever? How long will you look the other way?
19Ps 13:2 How long must I struggle with anguish in my soul, with sorrow in my heart every day? How long will my enemy have the upper hand?
19Ps 13:3 Turn and answer me, O LORD my God! Restore the sparkle to my eyes, or I will die.
19Ps 13:4 Don't let my enemies gloat, saying, "We have defeated him!" Don't let them rejoice at my downfall.
19Ps 13:5 But I trust in your unfailing love. I will rejoice because you have rescued me.
19Ps 13:6 I will sing to the LORD because he is good to me.
19Ps 14:1 [For the choir director£∫ A psalm of David.] Only fools say in their hearts, "There is no God." They are corrupt, and their actions are evil; not one of them does good!
19Ps 14:2 The LORD looks down from heaven on the entire human race; he looks to see if anyone is truly wise, if anyone seeks God.
19Ps 14:3 But no, all have turned away; all have become corrupt®Á. No one does good, not a single one! / ®ÁGreek version reads have become useless. Compare Rom 3.12
19Ps 14:4 Will those who do evil never learn? They eat up my people like bread and wouldn't think of praying to the LORD.
19Ps 14:5 Terror will grip them, for God is with those who obey him.
19Ps 14:6 The wicked frustrate the plans of the oppressed, but the LORD will protect his people.
19Ps 14:7 Who will come from Mount Zion to rescue Israel? When the LORD restores his people, Jacob will shout with joy, and Israel will rejoice.
19Ps 15:1 [A psalm of David.] Who may worship in your sanctuary, LORD? Who may enter your presence on your holy hill?
19Ps 15:2 Those who lead blameless lives and do what is right, speaking the truth from sincere hearts.
19Ps 15:3 Those who refuse to gossip or harm their neighbors or speak evil of their friends.
19Ps 15:4 Those who despise flagrant sinners, and honor the faithful followers of the LORD, and keep their promises even when it hurts.
19Ps 15:5 Those who lend money without charging interest, and who cannot be bribed to lie about the innocent. Such people will stand firm forever.
19Ps 16:1 [A psalm®Á of David.] Keep me safe, O God, for I have come to you for refuge. / ®ÁHebrew miktam. This may be a literary or musical term
19Ps 16:2 I said to the LORD, "You are my Master! Every good thing I have comes from you."
19Ps 16:3 The godly people in the land are my true heroes! I take pleasure in them!
19Ps 16:4 Troubles multiply for those who chase after other gods. I will not take part in their sacrifices of blood or even speak the names of their gods.
19Ps 16:5 LORD, you alone are my inheritance, my cup of blessing. You guard all that is mine.
19Ps 16:6 The land you have given me is a pleasant land. What a wonderful inheritance!
19Ps 16:7 I will bless the LORD who guides me; even at night my heart instructs me.
19Ps 16:8 I know the LORD is always with me. I will not be shaken, for he is right beside me.
19Ps 16:9 No wonder my heart is glad, and I rejoice®Á. My body rests in safety. / ®ÁGreek version reads and my tongue shouts his praises. Compare Acts 2.26
19Ps 16:10 For you will not leave my soul among the dead®Á or allow your holy one®Á to rot in the grave. / ®ÁHebrew in Sheol. ®ËOr your Holy One
19Ps 16:11 You will show me the way of life, granting me the joy of your presence and the pleasures of living with you forever®Á. / ®ÁGreek version reads You have shown me the way of life, / and you will fill me with the joy of your presence. Compare Acts 2.28
19Ps 17:1 [A prayer of David.] O LORD, hear my plea for justice. Listen to my cry for help. Pay attention to my prayer, for it comes from honest lips.
19Ps 17:2 Declare me innocent, for you see those who do right.
19Ps 17:3 You have tested my thoughts and examined my heart in the night. You have scrutinized me and found nothing wrong. I am determined not to sin in what I say.
19Ps 17:4 I have followed your commands, which keep me from following cruel and evil people.
19Ps 17:5 My steps have stayed on your path; I have not wavered from following you.
19Ps 17:6 I am praying to you because I know you will answer, O God. Bend down and listen as I pray.
19Ps 17:7 Show me your unfailing love in wonderful ways. By your mighty power you rescue those who seek refuge from their enemies.
19Ps 17:8 Guard me as you would guard your own eyes®Á. Hide me in the shadow of your wings. / ®ÁHebrew as the pupil of your eye
19Ps 17:9 Protect me from wicked people who attack me, from murderous enemies who surround me.
19Ps 17:10 They are without pity. Listen to their boasting!
19Ps 17:11 They track me down and surround me, watching for the chance to throw me to the ground.
19Ps 17:12 They are like hungry lions, eager to tear me apart - like young lions hiding in ambush.
19Ps 17:13 Arise, O LORD! Stand against them, and bring them to their knees! Rescue me from the wicked with your sword!
19Ps 17:14 By the power of your hand, O LORD, destroy those who look to this world for their reward. But satisfy the hunger of your treasured ones. May their children have plenty, leaving an inheritance for their descendants.
19Ps 17:15 Because I am righteous, I will see you. When I awake, I will see you face to face and be satisfied.
19Ps 18:1 [For the choir director£∫ A psalm of David, the servant of the LORD. He sang this song to the LORD on the day the LORD rescued him from all his enemies and from Saul. He sang.] I love you, LORD; you are my strength.
19Ps 18:2 The LORD is my rock, my fortress, and my savior; my God is my rock, in whom I find protection. He is my shield, the power that saves me, and my place of safety.
19Ps 18:3 I called on the LORD, who is worthy of praise, and he saved me from my enemies.
19Ps 18:4 The ropes of death entangled me; floods of destruction swept over me.
19Ps 18:5 The grave®Á wrapped its ropes around me; death laid a trap in my path. / ®ÁHebrew Sheol
19Ps 18:6 But in my distress I cried out to the LORD; yes, I prayed to my God for help. He heard me from his sanctuary; my cry to him reached his ears.
19Ps 18:7 Then the earth quaked and trembled. The foundations of the mountains shook; they quaked because of his anger.
19Ps 18:8 Smoke poured from his nostrils; fierce flames leaped from his mouth. Glowing coals blazed forth from him.
19Ps 18:9 He opened the heavens and came down; dark storm clouds were beneath his feet.
19Ps 18:10 Mounted on a mighty angelic being®Á, he flew, soaring on the wings of the wind. / ®ÁHebrew a cherub
19Ps 18:11 He shrouded himself in darkness, veiling his approach with dark rain clouds.
19Ps 18:12 Thick clouds shielded the brightness around him and rained down hail and burning coals®Á. / ®ÁOr and lightning bolts; also in 18.13
19Ps 18:13 The LORD thundered from heaven; the voice of the Most High resounded amid the hail and burning coals.
19Ps 18:14 He shot his arrows and scattered his enemies; his lightning flashed, and they were greatly confused. 
19Ps 18:15 Then at your command, O LORD, at the blast of your breath, the bottom of the sea could be seen, and the foundations of the earth were laid bare.
19Ps 18:16 He reached down from heaven and rescued me; he drew me out of deep waters.
19Ps 18:17 He rescued me from my powerful enemies, from those who hated me and were too strong for me.
19Ps 18:18 They attacked me at a moment when I was in distress, but the LORD supported me.
19Ps 18:19 He led me to a place of safety; he rescued me because he delights in me.
19Ps 18:20 The LORD rewarded me for doing right; he restored me because of my innocence.
19Ps 18:21 For I have kept the ways of the LORD; I have not turned from my God to follow evil.
19Ps 18:22 I have followed all his regulations; I have never abandoned his decrees.
19Ps 18:23 I am blameless before God; I have kept myself from sin.
19Ps 18:24 The LORD rewarded me for doing right. He has seen my innocence.
19Ps 18:25 To the faithful you show yourself faithful; to those with integrity you show integrity.
19Ps 18:26 To the pure you show yourself pure, but to the wicked you show yourself hostile.
19Ps 18:27 You rescue the humble, but you humiliate the proud.
19Ps 18:28 You light a lamp for me. The LORD, my God, lights up my darkness.
19Ps 18:29 In your strength I can crush an army; with my God I can scale any wall.
19Ps 18:30 God's way is perfect. All the LORD's promises prove true. He is a shield for all who look to him for protection.
19Ps 18:31 For who is God except the LORD? Who but our God is a solid rock?
19Ps 18:32 God arms me with strength, and he makes my way perfect.
19Ps 18:33 He makes me as surefooted as a deer, enabling me to stand on mountain heights.
19Ps 18:34 He trains my hands for battle; he strengthens my arm to draw a bronze bow.
19Ps 18:35 You have given me your shield of victory. Your right hand supports me; your help has made me great.
19Ps 18:36 You have made a wide path for my feet to keep them from slipping.
19Ps 18:37 I chased my enemies and caught them; I did not stop until they were conquered.
19Ps 18:38 I struck them down so they could not get up; they fell beneath my feet.
19Ps 18:39 You have armed me with strength for the battle; you have subdued my enemies under my feet.
19Ps 18:40 You placed my foot on their necks. I have destroyed all who hated me.
19Ps 18:41 They called for help, but no one came to their rescue. They even cried to the LORD, but he refused to answer.
19Ps 18:42 I ground them as fine as dust in the wind. I swept them into the gutter like dirt.
19Ps 18:43 You gave me victory over my accusers. You appointed me ruler over nations; people I don't even know now serve me.
19Ps 18:44 As soon as they hear of me, they submit; foreign nations cringe before me.
19Ps 18:45 They all lose their courage and come trembling from their strongholds.
19Ps 18:46 The LORD lives! Praise to my Rock! May the God of my salvation be exalted!
19Ps 18:47 He is the God who pays back those who harm me; he subdues the nations under me
19Ps 18:48 and rescues me from my enemies. You hold me safe beyond the reach of my enemies; you save me from violent opponents.
19Ps 18:49 For this, O LORD, I will praise you among the nations; I will sing praises to your name.
19Ps 18:50 You give great victories to your king; you show unfailing love to your anointed, to David and all his descendants forever.
19Ps 19:1 [For the choir director£∫ A psalm of David.] The heavens proclaim the glory of God. The skies display his craftsmanship.
19Ps 19:2 Day after day they continue to speak; night after night they make him known.
19Ps 19:3 They speak without a sound or word; their voice is never heard®Á. / ®ÁOr There is no speech or language where their voice is not heard
19Ps 19:4 Yet their message has gone throughout the earth, and their words to all the world. God has made a home in the heavens for the sun.
19Ps 19:5 It bursts forth like a radiant bridegroom after his wedding. It rejoices like a great athlete eager to run the race.
19Ps 19:6 The sun rises at one end of the heavens and follows its course to the other end. Nothing can hide from its heat.
19Ps 19:7 The instructions of the LORD are perfect, reviving the soul. The decrees of the LORD are trustworthy, making wise the simple.
19Ps 19:8 The commandments of the LORD are right, bringing joy to the heart. The commands of the LORD are clear, giving insight for living.
19Ps 19:9 Reverence for the LORD is pure, lasting forever. The laws of the LORD are true; each one is fair.
19Ps 19:10 They are more desirable than gold, even the finest gold. They are sweeter than honey, even honey dripping from the comb.
19Ps 19:11 They are a warning to your servant, a great reward for those who obey them.
19Ps 19:12 How can I know all the sins lurking in my heart? Cleanse me from these hidden faults.
19Ps 19:13 Keep your servant from deliberate sins! Don't let them control me. Then I will be free of guilt and innocent of great sin.
19Ps 19:14 May the words of my mouth and the meditation of my heart be pleasing to you, O LORD, my rock and my redeemer.
19Ps 20:1 [For the choir director£∫ A psalm of David.] In times of trouble, may the LORD answer your cry. May the name of the God of Jacob keep you safe from all harm.
19Ps 20:2 May he send you help from his sanctuary and strengthen you from Jerusalem®Á. / ®ÁHebrew Zion
19Ps 20:3 May he remember all your gifts and look favorably on your burnt offerings. Interlude
19Ps 20:4 May he grant your heart's desires and make all your plans succeed.
19Ps 20:5 May we shout for joy when we hear of your victory and raise a victory banner in the name of our God. May the LORD answer all your prayers.
19Ps 20:6 Now I know that the LORD rescues his anointed king. He will answer him from his holy heaven and rescue him by his great power.
19Ps 20:7 Some nations boast of their chariots and horses, but we boast in the name of the LORD our God.
19Ps 20:8 Those nations will fall down and collapse, but we will rise up and stand firm.
19Ps 20:9 Give victory to our king, O LORD! Answer our cry for help.
19Ps 21:1 [For the choir director£∫ A psalm of David.] How the king rejoices in your strength, O LORD! He shouts with joy because you give him victory.
19Ps 21:2 For you have given him his heart's desire; you have withheld nothing he requested. Interlude
19Ps 21:3 You welcomed him back with success and prosperity. You placed a crown of finest gold on his head.
19Ps 21:4 He asked you to preserve his life, and you granted his request. The days of his life stretch on forever.
19Ps 21:5 Your victory brings him great honor, and you have clothed him with splendor and majesty.
19Ps 21:6 You have endowed him with eternal blessings and given him the joy of your presence.
19Ps 21:7 For the king trusts in the LORD. The unfailing love of the Most High will keep him from stumbling.
19Ps 21:8 You will capture all your enemies. Your strong right hand will seize all who hate you.
19Ps 21:9 You will throw them in a flaming furnace when you appear. The LORD will consume them in his anger; fire will devour them.
19Ps 21:10 You will wipe their children from the face of the earth; they will never have descendants.
19Ps 21:11 Although they plot against you, their evil schemes will never succeed.
19Ps 21:12 For they will turn and run when they see your arrows aimed at them.
19Ps 21:13 Rise up, O LORD, in all your power. With music and singing we celebrate your mighty acts.
19Ps 22:1 [For the choir director£∫ A psalm of David, to be sung to the tune "Doe of the Dawn."] My God, my God, why have you abandoned me? Why are you so far away when I groan for help?
19Ps 22:2 Every day I call to you, my God, but you do not answer. Every night you hear my voice, but I find no relief.
19Ps 22:3 Yet you are holy, enthroned on the praises of Israel.
19Ps 22:4 Our ancestors trusted in you, and you rescued them.
19Ps 22:5 They cried out to you and were saved. They trusted in you and were never disgraced.
19Ps 22:6 But I am a worm and not a man. I am scorned and despised by all!
19Ps 22:7 Everyone who sees me mocks me. They sneer and shake their heads, saying,
19Ps 22:8 "Is this the one who relies on the LORD? Then let the LORD save him! If the LORD loves him so much, let the LORD rescue him!"
19Ps 22:9 Yet you brought me safely from my mother's womb and led me to trust you at my mother's breast.
19Ps 22:10 I was thrust into your arms at my birth. You have been my God from the moment I was born.
19Ps 22:11 Do not stay so far from me, for trouble is near, and no one else can help me.
19Ps 22:12 My enemies surround me like a herd of bulls; fierce bulls of Bashan have hemmed me in!
19Ps 22:13 Like lions they open their jaws against me, roaring and tearing into their prey.
19Ps 22:14 My life is poured out like water, and all my bones are out of joint. My heart is like wax, melting within me.
19Ps 22:15 My strength has dried up like sunbaked clay. My tongue sticks to the roof of my mouth. You have laid me in the dust and left me for dead.
19Ps 22:16 My enemies surround me like a pack of dogs; an evil gang closes in on me. They have pierced my hands and feet.
19Ps 22:17 I can count all my bones. My enemies stare at me and gloat.
19Ps 22:18 They divide my garments among themselves and throw dice®Á for my clothing. / ®ÁHebrew cast lots
19Ps 22:19 O LORD, do not stay far away! You are my strength; come quickly to my aid!
19Ps 22:20 Save me from the sword; spare my precious life from these dogs.
19Ps 22:21 Snatch me from the lion's jaws and from the horns of these wild oxen.
19Ps 22:22 I will proclaim your name to my brothers and sisters®Á. I will praise you among your assembled people. / ®ÁHebrew my brothers
19Ps 22:23 Praise the LORD, all you who fear him! Honor him, all you descendants of Jacob! Show him reverence, all you descendants of Israel!
19Ps 22:24 For he has not ignored or belittled the suffering of the needy. He has not turned his back on them, but has listened to their cries for help.
19Ps 22:25 I will praise you in the great assembly. I will fulfill my vows in the presence of those who worship you.
19Ps 22:26 The poor will eat and be satisfied. All who seek the LORD will praise him. Their hearts will rejoice with everlasting joy.
19Ps 22:27 The whole earth will acknowledge the LORD and return to him. All the families of the nations will bow down before him.
19Ps 22:28 For royal power belongs to the LORD. He rules all the nations.
19Ps 22:29 Let the rich of the earth feast and worship. Bow before him, all who are mortal, all whose lives will end as dust.
19Ps 22:30 Our children will also serve him. Future generations will hear about the wonders of the Lord.
19Ps 22:31 His righteous acts will be told to those not yet born. They will hear about everything he has done.
19Ps 23:1 [A psalm of David.] The LORD is my shepherd; I have all that I need.
19Ps 23:2 He lets me rest in green meadows; he leads me beside peaceful streams.
19Ps 23:3 He renews my strength. He guides me along right paths, bringing honor to his name.
19Ps 23:4 Even when I walk through the darkest valley®Á, I will not be afraid, for you are close beside me. Your rod and your staff protect and comfort me. / ®ÁOr the dark valley of death
19Ps 23:5 You prepare a feast for me in the presence of my enemies. You honor me by anointing my head with oil. My cup overflows with blessings.
19Ps 23:6 Surely your goodness and unfailing love will pursue me all the days of my life, and I will live in the house of the LORD forever.
19Ps 24:1 [A psalm of David.] The earth is the LORD's, and everything in it. The world and all its people belong to him.
19Ps 24:2 For he laid the earth's foundation on the seas and built it on the ocean depths.
19Ps 24:3 Who may climb the mountain of the LORD? Who may stand in his holy place?
19Ps 24:4 Only those whose hands and hearts are pure, who do not worship idols and never tell lies.
19Ps 24:5 They will receive the LORD's blessing and have a right relationship with God their savior.
19Ps 24:6 Such people may seek you and worship in your presence, O God of Jacob. Interlude
19Ps 24:7 Open up, ancient gates! Open up, ancient doors, and let the King of glory enter.
19Ps 24:8 Who is the King of glory? The LORD, strong and mighty; the LORD, invincible in battle.
19Ps 24:9 Open up, ancient gates! Open up, ancient doors, and let the King of glory enter.
19Ps 24:10 Who is the King of glory? The LORD of Heaven's Armies - he is the King of glory. Interlude
19Ps 25:1 ®Á[A psalm of David.] O LORD, I give my life to you. / ®ÁThis psalm is a Hebrew acrostic poem; each verse begins with a successive letter of the Hebrew alphabet
19Ps 25:2 I trust in you, my God! Do not let me be disgraced, or let my enemies rejoice in my defeat.
19Ps 25:3 No one who trusts in you will ever be disgraced, but disgrace comes to those who try to deceive others.
19Ps 25:4 Show me the right path, O LORD; point out the road for me to follow.
19Ps 25:5 Lead me by your truth and teach me, for you are the God who saves me. All day long I put my hope in you.
19Ps 25:6 Remember, O LORD, your compassion and unfailing love, which you have shown from long ages past.
19Ps 25:7 Do not remember the rebellious sins of my youth. Remember me in the light of your unfailing love, for you are merciful, O LORD.
19Ps 25:8 The LORD is good and does what is right; he shows the proper path to those who go astray.
19Ps 25:9 He leads the humble in doing right, teaching them his way.
19Ps 25:10 The LORD leads with unfailing love and faithfulness all who keep his covenant and obey his demands.
19Ps 25:11 For the honor of your name, O LORD, forgive my many, many sins.
19Ps 25:12 Who are those who fear the LORD? He will show them the path they should choose.
19Ps 25:13 They will live in prosperity, and their children will inherit the land.
19Ps 25:14 The LORD is a friend to those who fear him. He teaches them his covenant.
19Ps 25:15 My eyes are always on the LORD, for he rescues me from the traps of my enemies.
19Ps 25:16 Turn to me and have mercy, for I am alone and in deep distress.
19Ps 25:17 My problems go from bad to worse. Oh, save me from them all!
19Ps 25:18 Feel my pain and see my trouble. Forgive all my sins.
19Ps 25:19 See how many enemies I have and how viciously they hate me!
19Ps 25:20 Protect me! Rescue my life from them! Do not let me be disgraced, for in you I take refuge.
19Ps 25:21 May integrity and honesty protect me, for I put my hope in you.
19Ps 25:22 O God, ransom Israel from all its troubles.
19Ps 26:1 [A psalm of David.] Declare me innocent, O LORD, for I have acted with integrity; I have trusted in the LORD without wavering.
19Ps 26:2 Put me on trial, LORD, and cross-examine me. Test my motives and my heart.
19Ps 26:3 For I am always aware of your unfailing love, and I have lived according to your truth.
19Ps 26:4 I do not spend time with liars or go along with hypocrites.
19Ps 26:5 I hate the gatherings of those who do evil, and I refuse to join in with the wicked.
19Ps 26:6 I wash my hands to declare my innocence. I come to your altar, O LORD,
19Ps 26:7 singing a song of thanksgiving and telling of all your wonders.
19Ps 26:8 I love your sanctuary, LORD, the place where your glorious presence dwells.
19Ps 26:9 Don't let me suffer the fate of sinners. Don't condemn me along with murderers.
19Ps 26:10 Their hands are dirty with evil schemes, and they constantly take bribes.
19Ps 26:11 But I am not like that; I live with integrity. So redeem me and show me mercy.
19Ps 26:12 Now I stand on solid ground, and I will publicly praise the LORD.
19Ps 27:1 [A psalm of David.] The LORD is my light and my salvation - so why should I be afraid? The LORD is my fortress, protecting me from danger, so why should I tremble?
19Ps 27:2 When evil people come to devour me, when my enemies and foes attack me, they will stumble and fall.
19Ps 27:3 Though a mighty army surrounds me, my heart will not be afraid. Even if I am attacked, I will remain confident.
19Ps 27:4 The one thing I ask of the LORD - the thing I seek most - is to live in the house of the LORD all the days of my life, delighting in the LORD's perfections and meditating in his Temple.
19Ps 27:5 For he will conceal me there when troubles come; he will hide me in his sanctuary. He will place me out of reach on a high rock.
19Ps 27:6 Then I will hold my head high above my enemies who surround me. At his sanctuary I will offer sacrifices with shouts of joy, singing and praising the LORD with music.
19Ps 27:7 Hear me as I pray, O LORD. Be merciful and answer me!
19Ps 27:8 My heart has heard you say, "Come and talk with me." And my heart responds, "LORD, I am coming."
19Ps 27:9 Do not turn your back on me. Do not reject your servant in anger. You have always been my helper. Don't leave me now; don't abandon me, O God of my salvation!
19Ps 27:10 Even if my father and mother abandon me, the LORD will hold me close.
19Ps 27:11 Teach me how to live, O LORD. Lead me along the right path, for my enemies are waiting for me.
19Ps 27:12 Do not let me fall into their hands. For they accuse me of things I've never done; with every breath they threaten me with violence.
19Ps 27:13 Yet I am confident I will see the LORD's goodness while I am here in the land of the living.
19Ps 27:14 Wait patiently for the LORD. Be brave and courageous. Yes, wait patiently for the LORD.
19Ps 28:1 [A psalm of David.] I pray to you, O LORD, my rock. Do not turn a deaf ear to me. For if you are silent, I might as well give up and die.
19Ps 28:2 Listen to my prayer for mercy as I cry out to you for help, as I lift my hands toward your holy sanctuary.
19Ps 28:3 Do not drag me away with the wicked - with those who do evil - those who speak friendly words to their neighbors while planning evil in their hearts.
19Ps 28:4 Give them the punishment they so richly deserve! Measure it out in proportion to their wickedness. Pay them back for all their evil deeds! Give them a taste of what they have done to others.
19Ps 28:5 They care nothing for what the LORD has done or for what his hands have made. So he will tear them down, and they will never be rebuilt!
19Ps 28:6 Praise the LORD! For he has heard my cry for mercy.
19Ps 28:7 The LORD is my strength and shield. I trust him with all my heart. He helps me, and my heart is filled with joy. I burst out in songs of thanksgiving.
19Ps 28:8 The LORD gives his people strength. He is a safe fortress for his anointed king.
19Ps 28:9 Save your people! Bless Israel, your special possession®Á. Lead them like a shepherd, and carry them in your arms forever. / ®ÁHebrew Bless your inheritance
19Ps 29:1 [A psalm of David.] Honor the LORD, you heavenly beings®Á; honor the LORD for his glory and strength. / ®ÁHebrew you sons of God
19Ps 29:2 Honor the LORD for the glory of his name. Worship the LORD in the splendor of his holiness.
19Ps 29:3 The voice of the LORD echoes above the sea. The God of glory thunders. The LORD thunders over the mighty sea.
19Ps 29:4 The voice of the LORD is powerful; the voice of the LORD is majestic.
19Ps 29:5 The voice of the LORD splits the mighty cedars; the LORD shatters the cedars of Lebanon.
19Ps 29:6 He makes Lebanon's mountains skip like a calf; he makes Mount Hermon®Á leap like a young wild ox. / ®ÁHebrew Sirion, another name for Mount Hermon
19Ps 29:7 The voice of the LORD strikes with bolts of lightning.
19Ps 29:8 The voice of the LORD makes the barren wilderness quake; the LORD shakes the wilderness of Kadesh.
19Ps 29:9 The voice of the LORD twists mighty oaks®Á and strips the forests bare. In his Temple everyone shouts, "Glory!" / ®ÁOr causes the deer to writhe in labor
19Ps 29:10 The LORD rules over the floodwaters. The LORD reigns as king forever.
19Ps 29:11 The LORD gives his people strength. The LORD blesses them with peace.
19Ps 30:1 [A psalm of David. A song for the dedication of the Temple.] I will exalt you, LORD, for you rescued me. You refused to let my enemies triumph over me.
19Ps 30:2 O LORD my God, I cried to you for help, and you restored my health.
19Ps 30:3 You brought me up from the grave®Á, O LORD. You kept me from falling into the pit of death. / ®ÁHebrew from Sheol
19Ps 30:4 Sing to the LORD, all you godly ones! Praise his holy name.
19Ps 30:5 For his anger lasts only a moment, but his favor lasts a lifetime! Weeping may last through the night, but joy comes with the morning.
19Ps 30:6 When I was prosperous, I said, "Nothing can stop me now!"
19Ps 30:7 Your favor, O LORD, made me as secure as a mountain. Then you turned away from me, and I was shattered.
19Ps 30:8 I cried out to you, O LORD. I begged the Lord for mercy, saying,
19Ps 30:9 "What will you gain if I die, if I sink into the grave? Can my dust praise you? Can it tell of your faithfulness?
19Ps 30:10 Hear me, LORD, and have mercy on me. Help me, O LORD."
19Ps 30:11 You have turned my mourning into joyful dancing. You have taken away my clothes of mourning and clothed me with joy,
19Ps 30:12 that I might sing praises to you and not be silent. O LORD my God, I will give you thanks forever!
19Ps 31:1 [For the choir director£∫ A psalm of David.] O LORD, I have come to you for protection; don't let me be disgraced. Save me, for you do what is right.
19Ps 31:2 Turn your ear to listen to me; rescue me quickly. Be my rock of protection, a fortress where I will be safe.
19Ps 31:3 You are my rock and my fortress. For the honor of your name, lead me out of this danger.
19Ps 31:4 Pull me from the trap my enemies set for me, for I find protection in you alone.
19Ps 31:5 I entrust my spirit into your hand. Rescue me, LORD, for you are a faithful God.
19Ps 31:6 I hate those who worship worthless idols. I trust in the LORD.
19Ps 31:7 I will be glad and rejoice in your unfailing love, for you have seen my troubles, and you care about the anguish of my soul.
19Ps 31:8 You have not handed me over to my enemies but have set me in a safe place.
19Ps 31:9 Have mercy on me, LORD, for I am in distress. Tears blur my eyes. My body and soul are withering away.
19Ps 31:10 I am dying from grief; my years are shortened by sadness. Sin has drained my strength; I am wasting away from within.
19Ps 31:11 I am scorned by all my enemies and despised by my neighbors - even my friends are afraid to come near me. When they see me on the street, they run the other way.
19Ps 31:12 I am ignored as if I were dead, as if I were a broken pot.
19Ps 31:13 I have heard the many rumors about me, and I am surrounded by terror. My enemies conspire against me, plotting to take my life.
19Ps 31:14 But I am trusting you, O LORD, saying, "You are my God!"
19Ps 31:15 My future is in your hands. Rescue me from those who hunt me down relentlessly.
19Ps 31:16 Let your favor shine on your servant. In your unfailing love, rescue me.
19Ps 31:17 Don't let me be disgraced, O LORD, for I call out to you for help. Let the wicked be disgraced; let them lie silent in the grave®Á. / ®ÁHebrew in Sheol
19Ps 31:18 Silence their lying lips - those proud and arrogant lips that accuse the godly.
19Ps 31:19 How great is the goodness you have stored up for those who fear you. You lavish it on those who come to you for protection, blessing them before the watching world.
19Ps 31:20 You hide them in the shelter of your presence, safe from those who conspire against them. You shelter them in your presence, far from accusing tongues.
19Ps 31:21 Praise the LORD, for he has shown me the wonders of his unfailing love. He kept me safe when my city was under attack.
19Ps 31:22 In panic I cried out, "I am cut off from the LORD!" But you heard my cry for mercy and answered my call for help.
19Ps 31:23 Love the LORD, all you godly ones! For the LORD protects those who are loyal to him, but he harshly punishes the arrogant.
19Ps 31:24 So be strong and courageous, all you who put your hope in the LORD!
19Ps 32:1 [A psalm®Á of David.] Oh, what joy for those whose disobedience is forgiven, whose sin is put out of sight! / ®ÁHebrew maskil. This may be a literary or musical term
19Ps 32:2 Yes, what joy for those whose record the LORD has cleared of guilt®Á, whose lives are lived in complete honesty! / ®ÁGreek version reads of sin. Compare Rom 4.7
19Ps 32:3 When I refused to confess my sin, my body wasted away, and I groaned all day long.
19Ps 32:4 Day and night your hand of discipline was heavy on me. My strength evaporated like water in the summer heat. Interlude
19Ps 32:5 Finally, I confessed all my sins to you and stopped trying to hide my guilt. I said to myself, "I will confess my rebellion to the LORD." And you forgave me! All my guilt is gone. Interlude
19Ps 32:6 Therefore, let all the godly pray to you while there is still time, that they may not drown in the floodwaters of judgment.
19Ps 32:7 For you are my hiding place; you protect me from trouble. You surround me with songs of victory. Interlude
19Ps 32:8 The LORD says, "I will guide you along the best pathway for your life. I will advise you and watch over you.
19Ps 32:9 Do not be like a senseless horse or mule that needs a bit and bridle to keep it under control."
19Ps 32:10 Many sorrows come to the wicked, but unfailing love surrounds those who trust the LORD.
19Ps 32:11 So rejoice in the LORD and be glad, all you who obey him! Shout for joy, all you whose hearts are pure!
19Ps 33:1 Let the godly sing for joy to the LORD; it is fitting for the pure to praise him.
19Ps 33:2 Praise the LORD with melodies on the lyre; make music for him on the ten-stringed harp.
19Ps 33:3 Sing a new song of praise to him; play skillfully on the harp, and sing with joy.
19Ps 33:4 For the word of the LORD holds true, and we can trust everything he does.
19Ps 33:5 He loves whatever is just and good; the unfailing love of the LORD fills the earth.
19Ps 33:6 The LORD merely spoke, and the heavens were created. He breathed the word, and all the stars were born.
19Ps 33:7 He assigned the sea its boundaries and locked the oceans in vast reservoirs.
19Ps 33:8 Let the whole world fear the LORD, and let everyone stand in awe of him.
19Ps 33:9 For when he spoke, the world began! It appeared at his command.
19Ps 33:10 The LORD frustrates the plans of the nations and thwarts all their schemes.
19Ps 33:11 But the LORD's plans stand firm forever; his intentions can never be shaken.
19Ps 33:12 What joy for the nation whose God is the LORD, whose people he has chosen as his inheritance.
19Ps 33:13 The LORD looks down from heaven and sees the whole human race.
19Ps 33:14 From his throne he observes all who live on the earth.
19Ps 33:15 He made their hearts, so he understands everything they do.
19Ps 33:16 The best-equipped army cannot save a king, nor is great strength enough to save a warrior.
19Ps 33:17 Don't count on your warhorse to give you victory - for all its strength, it cannot save you.
19Ps 33:18 But the LORD watches over those who fear him, those who rely on his unfailing love.
19Ps 33:19 He rescues them from death and keeps them alive in times of famine.
19Ps 33:20 We put our hope in the LORD. He is our help and our shield.
19Ps 33:21 In him our hearts rejoice, for we trust in his holy name.
19Ps 33:22 Let your unfailing love surround us, LORD, for our hope is in you alone.
19Ps 34:1 ®Á[A psalm of David, regarding the time he pretended to be insane in front of Abimelech, who sent him away.] I will praise the LORD at all times. I will constantly speak his praises. / ®ÁThis psalm is a Hebrew acrostic poem; each verse begins with a successive letter of the Hebrew alphabet
19Ps 34:2 I will boast only in the LORD; let all who are helpless take heart.
19Ps 34:3 Come, let us tell of the LORD's greatness; let us exalt his name together.
19Ps 34:4 I prayed to the LORD, and he answered me. He freed me from all my fears.
19Ps 34:5 Those who look to him for help will be radiant with joy; no shadow of shame will darken their faces.
19Ps 34:6 In my desperation I prayed, and the LORD listened; he saved me from all my troubles.
19Ps 34:7 For the angel of the LORD is a guard; he surrounds and defends all who fear him.
19Ps 34:8 Taste and see that the LORD is good. Oh, the joys of those who take refuge in him!
19Ps 34:9 Fear the LORD, you his godly people, for those who fear him will have all they need.
19Ps 34:10 Even strong young lions sometimes go hungry, but those who trust in the LORD will lack no good thing.
19Ps 34:11 Come, my children, and listen to me, and I will teach you to fear the LORD.
19Ps 34:12 Does anyone want to live a life that is long and prosperous?
19Ps 34:13 Then keep your tongue from speaking evil and your lips from telling lies!
19Ps 34:14 Turn away from evil and do good. Search for peace, and work to maintain it.
19Ps 34:15 The eyes of the LORD watch over those who do right; his ears are open to their cries for help.
19Ps 34:16 But the LORD turns his face against those who do evil; he will erase their memory from the earth.
19Ps 34:17 The LORD hears his people when they call to him for help. He rescues them from all their troubles.
19Ps 34:18 The LORD is close to the brokenhearted; he rescues those whose spirits are crushed.
19Ps 34:19 The righteous person faces many troubles, but the LORD comes to the rescue each time.
19Ps 34:20 For the LORD protects the bones of the righteous; not one of them is broken!
19Ps 34:21 Calamity will surely overtake the wicked, and those who hate the righteous will be punished.
19Ps 34:22 But the LORD will redeem those who serve him. No one who takes refuge in him will be condemned.
19Ps 35:1 [A psalm of David.] O LORD, oppose those who oppose me. Fight those who fight against me.
19Ps 35:2 Put on your armor, and take up your shield. Prepare for battle, and come to my aid.
19Ps 35:3 Lift up your spear and javelin against those who pursue me. Let me hear you say, "I will give you victory!"
19Ps 35:4 Bring shame and disgrace on those trying to kill me; turn them back and humiliate those who want to harm me.
19Ps 35:5 Blow them away like chaff in the wind - a wind sent by the angel of the LORD.
19Ps 35:6 Make their path dark and slippery, with the angel of the LORD pursuing them.
19Ps 35:7 I did them no wrong, but they laid a trap for me. I did them no wrong, but they dug a pit to catch me.
19Ps 35:8 So let sudden ruin come upon them! Let them be caught in the trap they set for me! Let them be destroyed in the pit they dug for me.
19Ps 35:9 Then I will rejoice in the LORD. I will be glad because he rescues me.
19Ps 35:10 With every bone in my body I will praise him. "LORD, who can compare with you? Who else rescues the helpless from the strong? Who else protects the helpless and poor from those who rob them?"
19Ps 35:11 Malicious witnesses testify against me. They accuse me of crimes I know nothing about.
19Ps 35:12 They repay me evil for good. I am sick with despair.
19Ps 35:13 Yet when they were ill, I grieved for them. I denied myself by fasting for them, but my prayers returned unanswered.
19Ps 35:14 I was sad, as though they were my friends or family, as if I were grieving for my own mother.
19Ps 35:15 But they are glad now that I am in trouble; they gleefully join together against me. I am attacked by people I don't even know; they slander me constantly.
19Ps 35:16 They mock me and call me names; they snarl at me.
19Ps 35:17 How long, O Lord, will you look on and do nothing? Rescue me from their fierce attacks. Protect my life from these lions!
19Ps 35:18 Then I will thank you in front of the great assembly. I will praise you before all the people.
19Ps 35:19 Don't let my treacherous enemies rejoice over my defeat. Don't let those who hate me without cause gloat over my sorrow.
19Ps 35:20 They don't talk of peace; they plot against innocent people who mind their own business.
19Ps 35:21 They shout, "Aha! Aha! With our own eyes we saw him do it!"
19Ps 35:22 O LORD, you know all about this. Do not stay silent. Do not abandon me now, O Lord.
19Ps 35:23 Wake up! Rise to my defense! Take up my case, my God and my Lord.
19Ps 35:24 Declare me not guilty, O LORD my God, for you give justice. Don't let my enemies laugh about me in my troubles.
19Ps 35:25 Don't let them say, "Look, we got what we wanted! Now we will eat him alive!"
19Ps 35:26 May those who rejoice at my troubles be humiliated and disgraced. May those who triumph over me be covered with shame and dishonor.
19Ps 35:27 But give great joy to those who came to my defense. Let them continually say, "Great is the LORD, who delights in blessing his servant with peace!"
19Ps 35:28 Then I will proclaim your justice, and I will praise you all day long.
19Ps 36:1 [For the choir director£∫ A psalm of David, the servant of the LORD.] Sin whispers to the wicked, deep within their hearts. They have no fear of God at all.
19Ps 36:2 In their blind conceit, they cannot see how wicked they really are.
19Ps 36:3 Everything they say is crooked and deceitful. They refuse to act wisely or do good.
19Ps 36:4 They lie awake at night, hatching sinful plots. Their actions are never good. They make no attempt to turn from evil.
19Ps 36:5 Your unfailing love, O LORD, is as vast as the heavens; your faithfulness reaches beyond the clouds.
19Ps 36:6 Your righteousness is like the mighty mountains, your justice like the ocean depths. You care for people and animals alike, O LORD.
19Ps 36:7 How precious is your unfailing love, O God! All humanity finds shelter in the shadow of your wings.
19Ps 36:8 You feed them from the abundance of your own house, letting them drink from your river of delights.
19Ps 36:9 For you are the fountain of life, the light by which we see.
19Ps 36:10 Pour out your unfailing love on those who love you; give justice to those with honest hearts.
19Ps 36:11 Don't let the proud trample me or the wicked push me around.
19Ps 36:12 Look! Those who do evil have fallen! They are thrown down, never to rise again.
19Ps 37:1 ®Á[A psalm of David.] Don't worry about the wicked or envy those who do wrong. / ®ÁThis psalm is a Hebrew acrostic poem; each stanza begins with a successive letter of the Hebrew alphabet
19Ps 37:2 For like grass, they soon fade away. Like spring flowers, they soon wither.
19Ps 37:3 Trust in the LORD and do good. Then you will live safely in the land and prosper.
19Ps 37:4 Take delight in the LORD, and he will give you your heart's desires.
19Ps 37:5 Commit everything you do to the LORD. Trust him, and he will help you.
19Ps 37:6 He will make your innocence radiate like the dawn, and the justice of your cause will shine like the noonday sun.
19Ps 37:7 Be still in the presence of the LORD, and wait patiently for him to act. Don't worry about evil people who prosper or fret about their wicked schemes.
19Ps 37:8 Stop being angry! Turn from your rage! Do not lose your temper - it only leads to harm.
19Ps 37:9 For the wicked will be destroyed, but those who trust in the LORD will possess the land.
19Ps 37:10 Soon the wicked will disappear. Though you look for them, they will be gone.
19Ps 37:11 The lowly will possess the land and will live in peace and prosperity.
19Ps 37:12 The wicked plot against the godly; they snarl at them in defiance.
19Ps 37:13 But the Lord just laughs, for he sees their day of judgment coming.
19Ps 37:14 The wicked draw their swords and string their bows to kill the poor and the oppressed, to slaughter those who do right.
19Ps 37:15 But their swords will stab their own hearts, and their bows will be broken.
19Ps 37:16 It is better to be godly and have little than to be evil and rich.
19Ps 37:17 For the strength of the wicked will be shattered, but the LORD takes care of the godly.
19Ps 37:18 Day by day the LORD takes care of the innocent, and they will receive an inheritance that lasts forever.
19Ps 37:19 They will not be disgraced in hard times; even in famine they will have more than enough.
19Ps 37:20 But the wicked will die. The LORD's enemies are like flowers in a field - they will disappear like smoke.
19Ps 37:21 The wicked borrow and never repay, but the godly are generous givers.
19Ps 37:22 Those the LORD blesses will possess the land, but those he curses will die.
19Ps 37:23 The LORD directs the steps of the godly. He delights in every detail of their lives.
19Ps 37:24 Though they stumble, they will never fall, for the LORD holds them by the hand.
19Ps 37:25 Once I was young, and now I am old. Yet I have never seen the godly abandoned or their children begging for bread.
19Ps 37:26 The godly always give generous loans to others, and their children are a blessing.
19Ps 37:27 Turn from evil and do good, and you will live in the land forever.
19Ps 37:28 For the LORD loves justice, and he will never abandon the godly. He will keep them safe forever, but the children of the wicked will die.
19Ps 37:29 The godly will possess the land and will live there forever.
19Ps 37:30 The godly offer good counsel; they teach right from wrong.
19Ps 37:31 They have made God's law their own, so they will never slip from his path.
19Ps 37:32 The wicked wait in ambush for the godly, looking for an excuse to kill them.
19Ps 37:33 But the LORD will not let the wicked succeed or let the godly be condemned when they are put on trial.
19Ps 37:34 Put your hope in the LORD. Travel steadily along his path. He will honor you by giving you the land. You will see the wicked destroyed.
19Ps 37:35 I have seen wicked and ruthless people flourishing like a tree in its native soil.
19Ps 37:36 But when I looked again, they were gone! Though I searched for them, I could not find them!
19Ps 37:37 Look at those who are honest and good, for a wonderful future awaits those who love peace.
19Ps 37:38 But the rebellious will be destroyed; they have no future.
19Ps 37:39 The LORD rescues the godly; he is their fortress in times of trouble.
19Ps 37:40 The LORD helps them, rescuing them from the wicked. He saves them, and they find shelter in him.
19Ps 38:1 [A psalm of David, asking God to remember him.] O LORD, don't rebuke me in your anger or discipline me in your rage!
19Ps 38:2 Your arrows have struck deep, and your blows are crushing me.
19Ps 38:3 Because of your anger, my whole body is sick; my health is broken because of my sins.
19Ps 38:4 My guilt overwhelms me - it is a burden too heavy to bear.
19Ps 38:5 My wounds fester and stink because of my foolish sins.
19Ps 38:6 I am bent over and racked with pain. All day long I walk around filled with grief.
19Ps 38:7 A raging fever burns within me, and my health is broken.
19Ps 38:8 I am exhausted and completely crushed. My groans come from an anguished heart.
19Ps 38:9 You know what I long for, Lord; you hear my every sigh.
19Ps 38:10 My heart beats wildly, my strength fails, and I am going blind.
19Ps 38:11 My loved ones and friends stay away, fearing my disease. Even my own family stands at a distance.
19Ps 38:12 Meanwhile, my enemies lay traps to kill me. Those who wish me harm make plans to ruin me. All day long they plan their treachery.
19Ps 38:13 But I am deaf to all their threats. I am silent before them as one who cannot speak.
19Ps 38:14 I choose to hear nothing, and I make no reply.
19Ps 38:15 For I am waiting for you, O LORD. You must answer for me, O Lord my God.
19Ps 38:16 I prayed, "Don't let my enemies gloat over me or rejoice at my downfall."
19Ps 38:17 I am on the verge of collapse, facing constant pain.
19Ps 38:18 But I confess my sins; I am deeply sorry for what I have done.
19Ps 38:19 I have many aggressive enemies; they hate me without reason.
19Ps 38:20 They repay me evil for good and oppose me for pursuing good.
19Ps 38:21 Do not abandon me, O LORD. Do not stand at a distance, my God.
19Ps 38:22 Come quickly to help me, O Lord my savior.
19Ps 39:1 [For Jeduthun, the choir director£∫ A psalm of David.] I said to myself, "I will watch what I do and not sin in what I say. I will hold my tongue when the ungodly are around me."
19Ps 39:2 But as I stood there in silence - not even speaking of good things - the turmoil within me grew worse.
19Ps 39:3 The more I thought about it, the hotter I got, igniting a fire of words.
19Ps 39:4 "LORD, remind me how brief my time on earth will be. Remind me that my days are numbered - how fleeting my life is.
19Ps 39:5 You have made my life no longer than the width of my hand. My entire lifetime is just a moment to you; at best, each of us is but a breath." Interlude
19Ps 39:6 We are merely moving shadows, and all our busy rushing ends in nothing. We heap up wealth, not knowing who will spend it.
19Ps 39:7 And so, Lord, where do I put my hope? My only hope is in you.
19Ps 39:8 Rescue me from my rebellion. Do not let fools mock me.
19Ps 39:9 I am silent before you; I won't say a word, for my punishment is from you.
19Ps 39:10 But please stop striking me! I am exhausted by the blows from your hand.
19Ps 39:11 When you discipline us for our sins, you consume like a moth what is precious to us. Each of us is but a breath. Interlude
19Ps 39:12 Hear my prayer, O LORD! Listen to my cries for help! Don't ignore my tears. For I am your guest - a traveler passing through, as my ancestors were before me.
19Ps 39:13 Leave me alone so I can smile again before I am gone and exist no more.
19Ps 40:1 [For the choir director£∫ A psalm of David.] I waited patiently for the LORD to help me, and he turned to me and heard my cry.
19Ps 40:2 He lifted me out of the pit of despair, out of the mud and the mire. He set my feet on solid ground and steadied me as I walked along.
19Ps 40:3 He has given me a new song to sing, a hymn of praise to our God. Many will see what he has done and be amazed. They will put their trust in the LORD.
19Ps 40:4 Oh, the joys of those who trust the LORD, who have no confidence in the proud or in those who worship idols.
19Ps 40:5 O LORD my God, you have performed many wonders for us. Your plans for us are too numerous to list. You have no equal. If I tried to recite all your wonderful deeds, I would never come to the end of them.
19Ps 40:6 You take no delight in sacrifices or offerings. Now that you have made me listen, I finally understand®Á - you don't require burnt offerings or sin offerings. / ®ÁGreek text reads You have given me a body. Compare Heb 10.5
19Ps 40:7 Then I said, "Look, I have come. As is written about me in the Scriptures.
19Ps 40:8 I take joy in doing your will, my God, for your instructions are written on my heart."
19Ps 40:9 I have told all your people about your justice. I have not been afraid to speak out, as you, O LORD, well know.
19Ps 40:10 I have not kept the good news of your justice hidden in my heart; I have talked about your faithfulness and saving power. I have told everyone in the great assembly of your unfailing love and faithfulness.
19Ps 40:11 LORD, don't hold back your tender mercies from me. Let your unfailing love and faithfulness always protect me.
