23Is 45:19 I publicly proclaim bold promises. I do not whisper obscurities in some dark corner. I would not have told the people of Israel®Á to seek me if I could not be found. I, the Lord, speak only what is true and declare only what is right. / ®ÁHebrew of Jacob. See note on 14.1
23Is 45:20 °∞Gather together and come, you fugitives from surrounding nations. What fools they are who carry around their wooden idols and pray to gods that cannot save!
